3 Sec. 2. Section 71-812, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
4 2024, is amended to read:
5 71-812 (1) The Behavioral Health Services Fund is created. The fund
6 shall be administered by the division and shall contain cash funds
7 appropriated by the Legislature or otherwise received by the department
8 for the provision of behavioral health services from any other public or
9 private source and directed by the Legislature for credit to the fund.
10 Transfers may be made from the fund to the General Fund at the direction
11 of the Legislature.
12 (2) The Behavioral Health Services Fund shall be used to encourage
13 and facilitate the statewide development and provision of community-based
14 behavioral health services, including, but not limited to, (a) the
15 provision of grants, loans, and other assistance for such purpose and (b)
16 reimbursement to providers of such services.
17 (3)(a) Money transferred to the fund under section 76-903 shall be
18 used for housing-related assistance for very low-income adults with
19 serious mental illness or substance abuse disorder, except that if the
20 division determines that all housing-related assistance obligations under
21 this subsection have been fully satisfied, the division may distribute
22 any excess, up to twenty percent of such money, to regional behavioral
23 health authorities for acquisition or rehabilitation of housing to assist
24 such persons. The division shall manage and distribute such funds based
25 upon a formula established by the division, in consultation with regional
26 behavioral health authorities and the department, in a manner consistent
27 with and reasonably calculated to promote the purposes of the public
28 behavioral health system enumerated in section 71-803. The division shall
29 contract with each regional behavioral health authority for the provision
30 of such assistance. Each regional behavioral health authority may
31 contract with qualifying public, private, or nonprofit entities for the
