1 provision of such assistance.
2 (b) For purposes of this subsection:
3 (i) Adult with serious mental illness means a person eighteen years
4 of age or older who has, or at any time during the immediately preceding
5 twelve months has had, a diagnosable mental, behavioral, or emotional
6 disorder of sufficient duration to meet diagnostic criteria identified in
7 the most recent edition of the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of
8 Mental Disorders and which has resulted in functional impairment that
9 substantially interferes with or limits one or more major life functions.
10 Serious mental illness does not include DSM V codes, substance abuse
11 disorders, or developmental disabilities unless such conditions exist
12 concurrently with a diagnosable serious mental illness;
13 (ii) Housing-related assistance includes rental payments, utility
14 payments, security and utility deposits, landlord risk mitigation
15 payments, and other related costs and payments;
16 (iii) Landlord risk mitigation payment means a payment provided to a
17 landlord who leases or rents property to a very low-income adult with
18 serious mental illness which may be used to pay for excessive damage to
19 the rental property, any lost rent, any legal fees incurred by the
20 landlord in excess of the security deposit, or any other expenses
21 incurred by the landlord as a result of leasing or renting the property
22 to such individual; and
23 (iv) Very low-income means a household income of fifty percent or
24 less of the applicable median family income estimate as established by
25 the United States Department of Housing and Urban Development.
26 (4) Any money in the fund available for investment shall be invested
27 by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital
28 Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
29 Sec. 3. Original section 71-809, Reissue Revised Statutes of
